text: Kim So-young is a South Korean taekwondo practitioner. She won a gold medal in featherweight at the 1987 World Taekwondo Championships in Barcelona, and a gold medal in featherweight at the 1989 World Taekwondo Championships in Seoul. She won a gold medal at the 1988 Asian Taekwondo Championships in Kathmandu. ==References== ==External links== * Category:Year of birth missing (living people) Category:Living people Category:South Korean female taekwondo practitioners Category:World Taekwondo Championships medalists Category:Asian Taekwondo Championships medalists
